[5] Virus structure
Date: Thu 31 Mar 2016
Source: Science DOI: 10.1126/science.aaf5316 [edited]
http://science.sciencemag.org/content/early/2016/03/30/science.aaf5316


Devika Sirohi, Zhenguo Chen, Lei Sun, Thomas Klose, Theodore C. Pierson, Michael G. Rossmann, Richard J. Kuhn. The 3.8 Ã... resolution cryo-EM structure of Zika virus


Abstract
The recent rapid spread of Zika virus and its unexpected linkage to birth defects and an autoimmune-neurological syndrome has generated worldwide concern. Zika virus is a flavivirus like dengue, yellow fever and West Nile viruses. We present the 3.8Ã... resolution structure of mature Zika virus determined by cryo-electron microscopy. The structure of Zika virus is similar to other known flavivirus structures except for the around 10 amino acids that surround the Asn154 glycosylation site found in each of the 180 envelope glycoproteins that make up the icosahedral shell. The carbohydrate moiety associated with this residue, recognizable in the cryo-EM electron density, may function as an attachment site of the virus to host cells. This region varies not only among Zika virus strains but also in other flaviviruses and suggests that changes in this region influence virus transmission and disease.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The identification of the possible attachment site to host cells may provide a link to mosquito susceptibility to Zika virus and to one of the underlying mechanisms leading to disease in human hosts. Future advances into Zika virus structure will be of considerable interest. - Mod.TY]

